headlines.description: — Reserves Cole Anthony and Bol Bol each scored 17 points to lead the Orlando Magic to a 115-104 win over the Western Conference-leading Denver Nuggets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Subs Anthony, Bol key Magic's win over West-leading Nuggets

headlines.description: — Seeing his short-handed team struggle in a loss to Atlanta only made Phoenix coach Monty Williams all the more eager to see Kevin Durant in a Suns uniform.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 36 as Hawks beat short-handed Suns 116-107

headlines.description: — Spencer Dinwiddie scored 25 points in his first game since returning to Brooklyn and the Nets beat the Chicago Bulls 116-105 on Thursday night, hours after trading superstar Kevin Durant to Phoenix.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dinwiddie has 25 in Brooklyn return, Nets beat Bulls 116-105

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 38 points and 10 rebounds, and the Milwaukee Bucks rallied in the second half for their ninth consecutive victory, 115-106 over the Los Angeles Lakers without LeBron James on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks win 9th straight, hold off LeBron-less Lakers 115-106
